DIGEST
SB 64 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Hodges
Present law requires each public school governing authority to install cameras in certain
classrooms and to adopt policies that include provisions for determining to whom and under
what circumstances the video and audio recordings may be disclosed.
Proposed law retains present law and further requires both the superintendent and his
designee or two designees of the superintendent be present during the initial viewing of the
recordings after a request has been made.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Amends R.S. 17:1948(C)(5)(b); adds R.S. 17:1948(C)(5)(c))
